<p><strong>After considering all these biblical arguments, let's now use our common sense. <i>Neither demons, nor any
    creature can create anything</i></strong>. A demon cannot create a human body, <strong>give life to each
    cell</strong>, produce genital organs, make spermatozoids with chromosomes, genes, DNA, etc., to later introduce
    himself in that body, and have children with a woman, as said by the Russellists. This simply is not true.</p>
<p> Russellists also claim that according to Gn 6: 4, the sexual participation of demons, began the existence of giants
    on the Earth. <strong>This again is false. Otherwise all the children of demon-possessed men would be giants,
        something we know is not true.</strong></p>
<p> Russellists have not noticed that in this very verse it says that <strong>the giants existed before</strong> the
    sons of God married the daughters of men, and also after it.</p>
<p> "<strong>There were giants in the earth in those days</strong><i>; <strong>and also after that, when the sons of God
    came in unto the daughters of men</strong>, and they bare children to them, the same became mighty men which were of
    old, men of renown</i>." ( Gn 6: 4 )</p>
<p> As we know, during the Creation, God created <strong>only one man, Adam</strong>. According to the Russellists, God
    restarted His work with a second creation, <strong>but this time, instead of creating one man, He created thousands
        of them, and to boot, God created them with better genes than Adam, because their offspring were giants</strong>.
    Absurd!!</p>
<p> Something else to realize is that if these supposed demons, incarnated along a long period of time, then it have to
    be concluded that God worked for years or decades creating bodies for these abominable beings, instead of working
    only one day as when He created Adam. Absurd.</p>
<p><strong>Let's see another absurd claimed by Russellists. They insist that there is no soul, but only flesh. According
    to that, feelings, character and personality are just in the brain and not in the soul</strong>. If this was so,
    then they would have to admit the following: <strong>a)</strong> These newly created bodies, which were fashioned
    especially for demons, <strong>had a brain</strong>. In which case they were regular men, with their own
    individuality, feelings, and human personality, created by God, with the only purpose of being possessed by a demon.
    This is a blaspheme against God. <strong>b)</strong> The other alternative is that, to preclude those bodies from
    having a human personality, <strong>they were created without brains</strong>. In this case they have to believe the
    bizarre idea of a human body that performs perfectly well without a brain.</p>
<p><strong>In short, to think that this teaching is true means one of two: 1)</strong> either rebellious angels have a
    power and a wisdom equal to God, or <strong>2)</strong> God agreed with these demons in creating a body for them for
    the sole purpose of committing this horrid sin. Both ideas equally absurd and blasphemous.</p>
<p> This idea of "materialization" of angels must be related to the materialization of the spirits, as seen in the
    believers of spiritualism.</p>
